2:T74b,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is GitHub Copilot better than Qodo?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"It depends on your needs. GitHub Copilot scores 9.0 overall while Qodo scores 7.0. GitHub Copilot is best for developers wanting inline code suggestions and teams using GitHub workflows, while Qodo excels for quality-focused development teams and automated test generation."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Which is cheaper, GitHub Copilot or Qodo?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"GitHub Copilot starts at $10/mo and Qodo starts at $19/mo.  Qodo offers a free plan. Overall value depends on which features you need."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I switch from GitHub Copilot to Qodo?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, most users can migrate between these platforms. Both GitHub Copilot and Qodo support data import/export. The migration process typically involves exporting your data from one platform and importing it into the other. Some tools also offer migration assistance to make the transition smoother."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What do users say about GitHub Copilot vs Qodo?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"On review platforms, GitHub Copilot holds an overall rating of 9/10 and an ease of use score of 9/10. Qodo has an overall rating of 7/10 and ease of use score of 7/10. Users praise GitHub Copilot for seamless github integration and Qodo for strong test generation."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Which should I choose in 2026, GitHub Copilot or Qodo?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"In 2026, we recommend GitHub Copilot for most users based on its overall score and feature set. However, Qodo remains a strong contender, especially if you prioritize strong test generation. Try both free trials before committing."}}]}0:{"buildId":"oWPZTPCPUwZMl312gxRMA","rsc":["$","$1","c",{"children":[[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dange