7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both GitHub Copilot and Qodo share a solid foundation of core features including Code Review, Debugging, Test Generation, Multi Language. Where GitHub Copilot pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Autocomplete and Code Generation and Refactoring and Documentation, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. \n\nLooking at user ratings, GitHub Copilot holds an overall score of 9/10 and an ease of use score of 9/10, while Qodo scores 7/10 overall and 7/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, GitHub Copilot offers a more budget-friendly entry point at $10/mo, compared to Qodo's starting price of $19/mo. Qodo stands out by offering a free plan, giving you a risk-free way to explore the platform. GitHub Copilot requires a paid subscription from the start."}]]}]
