b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. GitHub Copilot is best suited for developers wanting inline code suggestions, teams using GitHub workflows, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Qodo, meanwhile, shines for quality focused development teams, automated test generation, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2021, GitHub Copilot describes itself as \"Your AI pair programmer that suggests code in real-time.\" Qodo, established in 2022, positions itself as \"AI-powered code integrity and test generation.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **GitHub Copilot** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (9.0 vs 7.0), more features (10 vs 6), more competitive pricing. However, this does not mean Qodo is a poor choice — far from it. Qodo excels in its own right, particularly for quality focused development teams and automated test generation.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value seamless github integration, go with GitHub Copilot. If strong test generation matters more to you, Qodo is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
